marta ivanova: Hey team - onboarding question. Trying to demo a streaming chat from my Windows laptop. Which key do we recommend? sandbox or hosted test key?

ryan choi: hi marta! sandbox for manual demos. hosted test keys are for CI/staging.

ben carter: note on Windows: some shells buffer stdout which can hide stream chunks. Use Git Bash or WSL, or run a node script. Also corp proxies can break chunked transfer.

marta ivanova: I tried node fetch and it seems to buffer until end. any example of a streaming Node snippet that works?

ben carter: quick node example:
```js
const res = await fetch('https://api.redwood.ai/v1/generate/stream',{
 method: 'POST',
 headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${process.env.SANDBOX_API_KEY}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
 body: JSON.stringify({ model: 'redwood-chat-1', input: 'hello', stream: true })
});
const reader = res.body.getReader();
